net.markenwerk.commons.collections.stacks

Class AbstractStack<Payload>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.markenwerk.commons.collections.sources.AbstractSource<Payload>
      • net.markenwerk.commons.collections.stacks.AbstractStack<Payload>
  • Type Parameters:
    Payload - The payload type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Payload>, Source<Payload>, Stack<Payload>, ProtectedIterable<Payload>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractLinkedStack

    public abstract class AbstractStack<Payload>
extends AbstractSource<Payload>
implements Stack<Payload>
    An AbstractStack is an abstract base implementation of Stack.

    An AbstractStack has two sets of protected methods.

    • A first set of abstract methods, prefixed with do, must be implemented by concrete implementations to perform the necessary structural modifications to the underlying data structure.
    • A second set of methods, prefixed with on, may be implemented by concrete implementations to perform additional actions after a structural modification has occurred.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Torsten Krause (tk at markenwerk dot net)

      • hashCode

        public final int hashCode()
        Description copied from interface: Stack
        Returns the hash code of this Stack.

        The hash code of a Stack is defined to be the result of the following calculation: 

         int hashCode = 1;
 Iterator<Payload> iterator = stack.iterator();
 while (iterator.hasNext()) {
        Payload payload = iterator.next();
        hashCode = 31 * hashCode + (null == payload ? 0 : payload.hashCode());
 }
        Specified by:
        hashCode in interface Stack<Payload>
        Overrides:
        hashCode in class Object
        Returns:
        The hash code of this Stack.
